subject: Display log using dlog.
commitMessage:
Display log using dlog.

Change-Id: I059c669dceb0b6b8b98e42c667563d9fd7d7effe

comments.message:
Patch Set 1:

Nicolas, could you please explain the necessity of this modification? Thanks!

Patch Set 1:

As connman-lib is a library, I propose this modification to separate log of this library and output of the application.

For example, I use the following command to do not disrupt output of capi-wifi-test with log of the libraries used by this application:

capi-wifi-test 2> capi-wifi-test.log

Patch Set 1:

Nicolas, I don't suggest you to submit this change for the reasons below:
1. Logically, the library belongs to the application process, so that the log should be output together with the application log.
2. Logically, stderr is standard error output, it seems not make much sense to output all the library log into standand error channel.
3. If you want to check the log only printed by the application, you can filter it out by some keywords.

Patch Set 1:

I think you did not understand my previous comment: the aim of this patch is to not disrupt user interaction of the application with debug traces.

May be a better solution will be to use dlog or do not have log enabled by default ?

Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

Nicolas, I prefer you to use dlog instead of stderr to print the library log, maybe you can refer to the file of include/common.h of platform/core/connectivity/bluetooth-frwk(devel branch) to see whether it can meet your requirement, thanks!
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.

and added services, so it needs to expose the added services
information in the library as well.

for the added services.

subject: manager: Check whether technology has already existed
commitMessage:
manager: Check whether technology has already existed

When the connman library is initialized, it will firstly sync
all technologies and save them, but if ConnMan daemon happens
to be launched just now, connman manager will receive the
“TechnologyAdded” signal for the technology which has already
been saved in the library. So it needs to check whether
technology has already existed when “TechnologyAdded“ signal
is received.

Change-Id: I084f8869a1e6f649a4962d66689bcfe1fce684dd
